<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910118-0035</DOCNO><DOCID>910118-0035.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Anglo American South Africa:   Combined Profits of Mines   Rose 2.1% in 4th Quarter</HL><DATE>01/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   ANGLY</CO><IN>PRECIOUS METALS, STONES, GOLD, SILVER (PCS)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Anglo American Corp. of South Africa said the combinedprofits of its six gold mines rose 2.1% in the fourth quarterof 1990 from the previous quarter.   Combined profits totaled 405.4 million rand ($157million), up from 397.1 million rand in the third quarter.</LP><TEXT>   Clem Sunter, chairman of the gold division, said at a newsconference that the group's gold mines had had success duringthe fourth quarter in reducing costs, which contributed tothe small increase in profit.</TEXT></DOC>